  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nRefactor WorldStateArchive to reflect Bonsai's expectation of a single persisted worldstate rather than Forest's multi-worldstate.  \r\n\r\n`getMutable()` overloads in the WorldStateArchive interface currently have side-effects for bonsai persisted world state.  As Bonsai is the future of storage for Besu, we should refactor the interface and usage of WorldStateArchive to reflect a 'head' worldstate, such that changes to the head worldstate must be explicit rather than side-effects of getting a mutable worldstate.  \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* refactor getMutable(***) to be side-effect free\r\n* annotate getMutable with `@MustBeClosed` to ensure via static analysis that mutable worldstates are closed\r\n* annotate `MutableWorldState.copy()` with `@MustBeClosed` to ensure via static analysis that copies of worldstates are closed\r\n* add to the interface an explicit  method to roll the persisted worldstate, such as `setHeadWorldState()`\r\n* update usages of getMutable which currently *expect* a side-effect of rolling the persisited world state to instead use an explicit `setHeadWorldState` method\r\n* implement setHeadWorldState method as a no-op for Forest\r\n",
